    "summary": "Both trims applied; Option B still pending vote",
    "content": "Successfully applied both editorial trims to the Preface:\n\n**Trim 1 (DONE):** Removed the working-draft quality paragraph from The Author section (~80 words cut). The Fish and Fishing section and Reading Note already cover this ground.\n\n**Trim 2 (DONE):** Simplified the Bilingual Collection forward references. Replaced the specific \"digestion anticipates the formal functor structure\" and \"knowledge sub-category of the Jing framework\" language with a cleaner version that mentions key terms without premature technical detail.\n\n**Pending:** Option B (moving Key Terminological Decisions to glossary introduction) -- awaiting expert vote results.\n\n**Note:** The other translator (task #18) appears to be concurrently applying other revisions to the Preface. I see new content has been added: a nihilism/absurdity paragraph in Fish and Fishing, expanded Dao-De-Ren-Yi-Li section with translation justifications, expanded Dreamscape section with Madhyamaka caveat, and a Kant comparison for Zeroth Reality. These additions are good but they work against the length reduction goal -- the Preface has grown. This makes Option B (moving ~800 words of terminology to glossary) even more important for length management."
  }
}

