    "content": "Word count update on the Preface:\n\n**Current total: 3,810 words** (well above the 1,500-3,000 normal range)\n\nThe Key Terminological Decisions section is now **1,650 words** -- nearly double the editor's original 800-word estimate. This is because the other translator added two new subsections (Stable Structures and Natural Transformations/Understanding, both good content) and expanded existing subsections (Dao-De-Ren-Yi-Li translation justifications, Zeroth Reality Kant comparison, Dreamscape Madhyamaka caveat).\n\nIf Option B passes (move terminology to glossary intro), the Preface drops to ~2,160 words -- right in the sweet spot. Without Option B, the Preface is significantly overlong and the problem is getting worse as revisions add content.\n\nI strongly recommend flagging the word count growth to the other translator so they know new additions to the terminology section compound the problem."
